# Implementation Plan - Phase 6: Real-time Q&A Chat

This plan details the design and changes to build a real-time Q&A Chat system inside the learning classroom, allowing students to ask questions, post threaded replies, flag inappropriate content, and allow mentors/admins to moderate chat rooms in real time.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> - **JWT WebSockets Auth**: Native browser WebSockets do not support custom headers. The JWT token will be passed as a query parameter (e.g. `?token=jwt_access_token`). We will write a custom `JWTAuthMiddleware` to parse and decode the token server-side.
> - **InMemory Channels for Dev**: We use `channels.layers.InMemoryChannelLayer` for local development. This works without a Redis server setup.
> - **Moderation Guardrails**: Mentors and Admins can flag, hide, or delete messages. Students can only see non-hidden messages.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Django Channels & Routing Configuration

#### [NEW] [channels_middleware.py](file:///c:/Users/shans/CascadeProjects/Online_Education_Platform/backend/users/channels_middleware.py)
- Implement `JWTAuthMiddleware`:
  - Intercepts incoming WebSocket connection requests.
  - Extracts the `token` parameter from `scope['query_string']`.
  - Decodes it using Django SimpleJWT's HS256 validation to authenticate the user.
  - Attaches the authenticated user (or `AnonymousUser`) to `scope['user']`.

#### [MODIFY] [asgi.py](file:///c:/Users/shans/CascadeProjects/Online_Education_Platform/backend/core/asgi.py)
- Replace `AuthMiddlewareStack` with our `JWTAuthMiddleware` to handle JWT WebSocket authentication.

#### [NEW] [consumers.py](file:///c:/Users/shans/CascadeProjects/Online_Education_Platform/backend/chat/consumers.py)
- Create `ChatConsumer` inheriting from `AsyncJsonWebsocketConsumer`:
  - **`connect()`**:
    - Validates user role and course enrollment / ownership access using `database_sync_to_async`.
    - Automatically lazy-creates the `ChatRoom` if it doesn't exist.
    - Joins the channel group `chat_{course_id}`.
  - **`receive_json()`**:
    - Processes payload actions:
      1. `"send_message"`: Saves `ChatMessage` (with optional `parent_id` for threads) and broadcasts to the room.
      2. `"flag_message"`: Sets `is_flagged_abuse=True` and broadcasts.
      3. `"hide_message"`: (Mentor/Admin only) Sets `is_hidden=True` and broadcasts.
      4. `"delete_message"`: (Sender/Mentor/Admin only) Deletes message and broadcasts.

#### [MODIFY] [routing.py](file:///c:/Users/shans/CascadeProjects/Online_Education_Platform/backend/chat/routing.py)
- Route the consumer:
  - Add `re_path(r'^ws/course/(?P<course_id>[^/.]+)/qa/$', consumers.ChatConsumer.as_asgi())` to `websocket_urlpatterns`.

